item.title: No title
item.description: Every time I tell someone what I studied at University I have the same conversation. I've had it 4 times in the last week. So I thought I'd get my thoughts down - it'll save me time as I can just point people to the answer, but more than that, it's actually worth thinking about. In these days of vocational degrees, is there any value at all in studying something for its own sake?
